I use URI templates as a component of my hypermedia controls. They let me d=
ynamically communicate to clients how to build certain URIs. They are more =
powerful than mere URI lists, which are limited in the number of URIs you c=
an communicate, and HTML forms, which can only express a more limited set o=
f URIs (i.e., the variable part has to use query parameters).

Here is such=
 a use case of URI template : http://example.com/stockquote/{symbol}  

